{"id":13738,"date":"2025-12-06T07:51:15","date_gmt":"2025-12-06T04:51:15","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/emuseum.torus.kz\/exhibit\/68da7f025a1fa3c87-en\/"},"modified":"2025-12-31T12:39:16","modified_gmt":"2025-12-31T09:39:16","slug":"68da7f025a1fa3c87-en","status":"publish","type":"exhibit","link":"https:\/\/e-museum.kz\/en\/exhibit\/68da7f025a1fa3c87-en\/","title":{"rendered":"Book."},"content":{"rendered":"<p>\u0412\u043e\u043e\u043a. This book by journalist and writer Oraz Ismailov compiles essays, short stories, and novellas dedicated to historical figures and notable workers who played important roles in Kazakhstan\u2019s history. The work combines historical insight and artistic expression, making it a valuable resource for readers interested in the country\u2019s history, culture, and society.The cover features an image of a man in military uniform (depicting Shoqan Walikhanov) sitting on a rock in a natural setting. In the background, mountains and a river are visible. The book\u2019s title, \u201cAltyn Beldeu\u201d, is written in large, diagonal letters. The cover design is done in warm and light tones.  On the first page, the author wrote in red ink: \u201c\u04e8\u0437\u0456\u043c\u0434\u0435 \u049b\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0442\u044b\u043d \u2018\u0421\u04af\u0439\u0456\u043d\u0448\u0456\u2019 \u0434\u0430\u043d\u0430 27 \u049b\u044b\u0440\u043a\u04af\u0439\u0435\u043a 2005 \u0436 \u0441\u0435\u0439\u0441\u0435\u043d\u0431\u0456\u201d (\u201cPersonal copy \u2018S\u00fcyinshi\u2019, September 27, 2005, Tuesday\u201d) and signed it. A personal library stamp is placed at the bottom of the page.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"featured_media":0,"menu_order":0,"template":"","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"","ast-site-content-layout":"default","site-content-style":"default","site-sidebar-style":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-be